project.title: CyberPunk District 9
project.description: The power is out.  Can you turn it back on?

values.message:
All Locations Tagged.  Great Job!
We have your next assignment.
When you are ready, pick up
the phone with our out of order sign
and our tag on the side.
Talk to you soon.

values.text:
I partied too hard last night 
at the penthouse on the top floor.  
My head is pounding and I cannot find 
the key that activates the mixing board.   
This is too much to handle right now.  
Going to sleep off this hangover.   
Catch ya later.

values.message: Software Installed

values.onClickText: Find Blue Access Key To Play Music

values.message: DJ System Activation Card

This must be the tag (graffiti) used by the gang.  
Anywhere you see this mischief must not be far behind.

Looks like there was break in and is under repairs.  
Do I see something in there?  
Maybe we can find the key to unlock these gates

values.onClickText: Power Control.  Locked. Find Red Access Key

values.message:
Did you see that!
The city power just went out.  See what you can discover.

Congratulations! You did it!  
Power has been restored!
You should ask the local authorities if there is a reward.
Check out the view from the penthouse. 
The elevators should be working now.

Locked!  What is that device on the back of the monitor.
Maybe the tags have clues as to what the passcode would be?

values.text:
Dude, where did you go?  
I thought the police caught me but turned out to be the 
DJ we saw yesterday blackout drunk.  
Ran right into me.  Our stuff went all over the ground.  
Anyway, I am breaking into one of the sushi restaurants 
for some to go food.  Want anything?

values.message:
Some trouble makers thought it would be funny to cut power to the lower city.  
Can you help me restore order to the area?  
Look for graffiti like you see next to me.  
That marks where they have been.  
Maybe you can find some clues.

Hey Kid.  They call me LT.  I am a member of The Resistance
Great job down there.  You unraveled our work like it was nothing.
We thought it would take days for them to figure it out.
I heard they promoted you to Citizen for your good deed.
I can recognize an asset when I see one.
Will you join us?

Your first task:
Spread a specially coded message throughout the city. 
Throw up tags anywhere you see trash cans.
Our agents will know what it means.
I will keep track from up here.

Spread a specially coded message throughout the city. 
Throw up tags anywhere you see trash cans.
Our agents will know what it means.
I will keep track from up here.
Your loss.
Access Granted.  Welcome, Citizen!

Great work restoring power to the lower city.
As a thank you we have promoted your status to Citizen.
Here is your official ID card.  This will give you access to the upper city.

We need you to come in.  
We have a regional office in the bus stop building.
The access code is rotating.  It can be found
as the high score on one of the arcade games.  
Player name Artemis.  Their score will be the code.
See you soon.

Use this to gain access to Black Building
Make sure to look for anything else useful while in there
Use Yellow Data Drive to install backdoor software on government computers

Welcome to the Resistance Base

We have a plan to take the fight to the government. 
Infecting their computers with a backdoor gain us what we need.

With your new status as Citizen, you are in the position to do it.

You will find what you need in the cabinets over there.
Black Building Access ID Chip

Great Job.  All computers infected.
Return to the resistance to base.

Congratulations!  Mission Accomplished!

The Resistance thanks you for playing.
They can bring the fight to the heart of the government now.

Stay tuned for more missions in the future.
Please continue to explore the city.
Restricted Areas Access ID Chip
Cheater Cheater Pumpkin Eater
Building Secure
